race.comment: SUMMIT (5) peaks and has switched back from Waller's Victorian barn on a 25-day return. Has provincial form stacks right up and Ben Thompson's booking suggests the well-bred gelding is pleasing the yard. FUNKY ZEBRA (2) resumes for the Munce barn and found a place in a recent Doomben trial. He's been gelded and maps for the run of the race. Showed enough on debut to say he can make the finish. Stablemate PENSIERO (7) has been struggling to find her best form but hits this contest at peak fitness and she went better at the Sunshine Coast last time. LOPE BY NIGHT (3) needed the first up run and we will see improvement today. He draws the rail and has pieces of form that would see him in the money.
